
Task Management System

Overview

A RESTful API for managing tasks, built using Express.js, MongoDB, and Mongoose, with JWT authentication.

Endpoints

Tasks
- *POST /tasks*: Create a new task
    - Request Body: `{ description: string, completed: boolean }`
    - Response: `201 Created` with task object
    
- *GET /tasks*: Retrieve all tasks
    - Response: `200 OK` with array of task objects

- *PUT /tasks/:id*: Update a task
    - Request Body: `{ description: string, completed: boolean }`
    - Response: `200 OK` with updated task object

- *DELETE /tasks/:id*: Delete a task
    - Response: `204 No Content`

Authentication
- *POST /auth/signup*: Create a new user account
    - Request Body: `{ username: string, password: string }`
    - Response: `201 Created` with user object
- *POST /auth/login*: Authenticate a user and return a JWT token
    - Request Body: `{ username: string, password: string }`
    - Response: `200 OK` with JWT token

Models

Task
- *description*: string
- *completed*: boolean

User
- *username*: string
- *password*: string (hashed)

Authentication

- JWT tokens are used for authentication
- Tokens are generated upon successful login and must be included in the `Authorization` header for protected routes
